### HYMN LIII

#### A prayer for recovery and preservation of health and security

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0605301">1</span></span>May Heaven
and Earth, wise pair, may lofty Sukra grant me  
   this thing by reason of the guerdon.  
  May Agni, Soma mark through this libation: may Vāyu,  
  Savitar, and Bhaga guard us.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0605302">2</span></span>Again return
to us our breath and spirit, again come back to us  
   our life and vision!  
  Vaisvānara, unscathed, our bodies' guardian, stand between us  
   and every woe and danger!  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0605303">3</span></span>We are again
united with our bodies, with happy mind, with  
   spirit, strength, and splendour. <span id="page_a225">p.
a225</span>  
  May Tvashtar here make room for us, and freedom and smooth  
   whate'er is injured in our bodies.

